rawContent:
I find it irksome when I hear people say that accepting gay people is what brought on this entire mess of grooming, gender ideology, & queer theory. The good ole slippery slope.

Here’s why it wasn’t. (Very TLDR‼️)

Allow me to make an analogy. Can I tell you a story? I’m gonna tell you a little story…

So imagine a little old house tucked away at the corner of the city. And in it resides an unhappy married couple.

Person A is a shut-in. Let’s call her Phylis. Maybe she’s got a controlling husband, Person B. His name is Arthur.

So Arthur is basically like a Covid Karen. And for years he has told her, “You can never leave the house!!! It’s not safe. You’ll get LITERALLY murdered!!!!! You can never step out the front door! The sky will fall on you!!!! Hoodlums will find you! The air isn’t safe! There’s radiation! The only way to stay safe is to never go out into the world”.

So he keeps her locked down.

But one day, Phylis decides to start a new life. She leaves the house! And instead of doing healthy or productive things… she overcompensates and overindulges in this new freedom. She goes FULL Courtney Love! I mean, she LOSES. HER. SHIT.

She decides to go play in traffic. She shoots heroin. She drinks a bottle of poison. She decides to read spoken word poetry for ISIS while doing a naked little titty dance! She hangs around dark alleyways in the middle of the night. She jumps out of a plane without a parachute. She goes on a date with OJ!

So naturally… the bitch gets herself killed!

And Arthur, while mourning his late wife, is like “See? Never should’ve let her leave the house!”

(Ahhh, see? We’re getting towards the point…)

And THAT is what has happened with basic gay rights morphing into forced cake baking and Drag Queen Story Hour and double mastectomies for 12 year olds.

We have allowed our culture to play in traffic and drink poison. We have been Phylis’d! That is the root problem.

We removed all boundaries and standards of society, nobody would say “NO!”, and that’s what brought us here. Allowing adults the freedom to love other adults is not.

You cannot do something virtuous, then follow it with a mountain of degeneracy, and then blame the prior virtuous thing for what occurred. It is our choices afterwards that matter.

The answer was never to stay locked inside, just as the answer was never to shun people for their sexual orientation. If anything, that sort of misguided repression only fueled the negative outcome.

There are so many factors at play in what got us here, and there is plenty of blame to go around. Let’s not forget conservative leaders abandoning every institution in America and ceding all control to the radical left. Not to mention the uniparty fucks who stand to profit from the woke cultural revolution! This crap has even invaded your churches! So there’s blame on them as well. There is also blame on gay people who have stayed silent and allowed this to happen in our name. Lots of blame to go around — but what matters now is course correction.

Adults being free to love whatever consenting adults they’d like is the cornerstone of liberty. It is so basic and fundamental that without it, there isn’t much else. 

So I do hope that the average person sees the difference, and knows how many of us #GaysAgainstGroomers are deadset against the atrocities that are happening in our name. And I also want people to realize that my relationship has played no role in that.

We are standing here in a moment where the slippery has LONG since sloped… but it didn’t have to.

What matters now is how we go forward. For those who say that we just need to roll back tolerance of gay people — it is not only incorrect and counterproductive, but it only serves to help the butchers, the bakers, and the indoctrinators.
